# Implementation Plan: DLHC Public-Facing Pages

This document outlines the approach for implementing the remaining public pages and shared components of the DLHC platform, adhering strictly to a professional, B2B, product-focused design language. We will avoid marketing exaggerations, massive hero sections, decorative gradients, and instead focus on clarity, utility, and a clean SaaS aesthetic inspired by Microsoft 365, Atlassian, and Stripe.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]  
> Please review the proposed **Content Updates** for the Home Page and the **Component Strategy**. Ensure the new professional copy aligns perfectly with your expectations before we proceed to coding.
> Also, confirm if you would like me to use `lucide-react` for any minimal functional icons (e.g., checkmarks in pricing tables, user roles), as it is already in `package.json`.

## Proposed Changes

We will organize the implementation into three phases: Shared Components, Core Public Pages, and Legal/Auth Pages.

---

### Phase 1: Shared Components & Layout

We need to build the foundational UI components to ensure consistency across all public routes.

#### [NEW] `src/components/public/PublicNavbar.tsx`
*   **Purpose:** A responsive top navigation bar.
*   **Design:** Minimalist white/dark background with a slight bottom border. Left-aligned logo, center-aligned links (Features, Templates, Pricing), right-aligned Login/Register buttons. No massive padding.

#### [NEW] `src/components/public/PublicFooter.tsx`
*   **Purpose:** Standard SaaS footer.
*   **Design:** Structured grid with column links (Product, Resources, Legal, Company) and a simple copyright line. Muted text colors.

#### [NEW] `src/components/public/CookieBanner.tsx`
*   **Purpose:** GDPR/CCPA compliant unobtrusive banner.
*   **Design:** Fixed bottom strip, compact, with "Accept" and "Manage Preferences" buttons.

#### [NEW] `src/components/public/PricingCard.tsx`
*   **Purpose:** Reusable component for both the Pricing page and the Home page preview.
*   **Design:** Clean border, explicit price, bulleted feature list (functional check icons), primary/secondary button CTA depending on the tier.

#### [NEW] `src/components/public/TemplateCard.tsx`
*   **Purpose:** Standardized display for templates in the gallery.
*   **Design:** Crisp thumbnail with a subtle 1px border. Title, Category tag. Simple "Preview" / "Use Template" hover actions (no excessive animation).

#### [MODIFY] `src/app/(public)/layout.tsx`
*   **Change:** Integrate `PublicNavbar`, `PublicFooter`, and `CookieBanner` into the public layout wrapper so they automatically apply to all child pages.

---

### Phase 2: Core Public Pages

#### [MODIFY] `src/app/(public)/page.tsx` (Home Page)
*   **Refactoring Current Implementation:**
    *   **Hero Section:** Change headline from *"Create Professional Letterheads in Minutes"* to *"Standardize Company Letterheads"*. Change subheadline to *"Create, manage, and export approved corporate letterheads across your organization."* Reduce excessive `py-24` padding to a more compact `py-16`.
    *   **Features Overview:** Convert the current generic "Why Choose DLHC?" to a practical list: "Drag & Drop Editor", "Role-Based Team Management", "PDF & DOCX Export". Remove emojis (✨, 🏢, 📄) and replace them with standard, professional `lucide-react` icons (e.g., `LayoutTemplate`, `Users`, `FileDown`).
    *   **New Section (Pricing Preview):** Add a compact section showing the 3 tiers using the new `PricingCard` component.
    *   **New Section (Final CTA):** A structured, simple banner: "Manage templates, teams, and exports from a centralized workspace." with a "Get Started" button.

#### [NEW] `src/app/(public)/templates/page.tsx`
*   **Purpose:** The Templates Gallery.
*   **Structure:**
    *   Compact Header: "Template Library"
    *   Filter Bar: Search input and Category pills (Corporate, Medical, Legal, Minimalist, Creative).
    *   Grid of `TemplateCard` components.
    *   Bottom CTA for registration.

#### [NEW] `src/app/(public)/pricing/page.tsx`
*   **Purpose:** Dedicated Pricing Page.
*   **Structure:**
    *   Header: "Transparent Pricing for Organizations".
    *   Grid of 3 `PricingCard` components (Free, Pro, Enterprise).
    *   Feature Comparison Table (using standard HTML `<table>` styled with Tailwind for easy scanning).
    *   FAQ Accordion.

#### [NEW] `src/app/(public)/features/page.tsx`
*   **Purpose:** Product Capabilities.
*   **Structure:** Alternating left/right layout (or simple stacked sections) detailing:
    *   Drag & Drop Editor (with placeholder for UI screenshot)
    *   Team Management (Admin/Editor/Viewer workflows)
    *   Exporting (PDF/DOCX)
    *   Integrations

